    <p><strong>Strengths:</strong> High conceptual equivalence, Near‑identical difficulty, Excellent structural validity, Accurate answer key</p>
    <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong> Slight wording ambiguities, Limited distinctness; could vary context more, Minor distractor plausibility issues</p>
  </div>

